Japan’s Wages Declined 1.4% in April From a Year Earlier

-- B y   A k i   I t o
-- 
2011-05-31T01:30:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/japan-s-wages-declined-1-4-in-april-from-a-year-earlier.html
Japan ’s monthly wages including
overtime and bonuses dropped 1.4 percent in April from a year
earlier to 272,255 yen ($3,367), the second straight decline,
the Labor Ministry said today in  Tokyo .  To contact the reporter on this story:
